      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's an interesting way to put it. so u're saying that things like capitalism and democracy are basically the benchmarks for being \"modern\"? i was wondering if u could elaborate on why non-western cultures are usually categorized as \"primitive\" in this framework. is it just because they don't have those specific western structures?",
